32:24.910 --> 32:28.814 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Osman Kozlic is
the imam
of this World Heritage Site.

32:28.914 --> 32:34.419 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
What is your message
specifically to the Serbs
in terms of reconciliation and
trying to move

32:34.519 --> 32:36.254 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
on?

32:36.354 --> 32:41.526 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
OSMAN KOZLIC: Our mosques, our
cathedrals,
our temples belong to all of
them, belong

32:41.626 --> 32:52.270 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to us. This is holy place, not
only for me,
as a Muslim, but it's holy place
for Catholics,

32:52.370 --> 33:00.612 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for Orthodox Serbs. And if we
are -- think
in that way, we have a good
future.

33:00.712 --> 33:06.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: The mosque has
special meaning
for 21-year-old Emir
Galijasevic, even though

33:06.251 --> 33:11.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
he was born just a year before
the war ended.
His family came from Banja Luka
and were among

33:11.790 --> 33:14.025 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
those driven out during the
ethnic cleansing.

33:14.125 --> 33:17.796 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
EMIR GALIJASEVIC, Bosnia: All
the criminals
who had done bad things in the
war had to

33:17.896 --> 33:24.102 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be going from the court. But I
still think
people can still live together.
We can still

33:24.202 --> 33:34.713 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
be friends and work together and
be as a mirror
to other place in Europe, that
multiculturalism

33:34.813 --> 33:41.386 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can live, and it's, I think, the
best example
of this is this mosque in this
town.

33:41.486 --> 33:46.558 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But segregation
has been
exacerbated by economic
stagnation. On both

33:46.658 --> 33:52.931 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
sides of the tangible partition,
unemployment
is sky-high, especially among
the young. When

33:53.031 --> 33:58.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
part of Yugoslavia, this region
was reasonably
productive. Now it's anything
but.

33:58.670 --> 34:02.974 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Potential investors are
frightened away by
corruption and political
uncertainty.

34:03.074 --> 34:10.215 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Pero Slavnic, a former major in
the Bosnian
Serb army, is campaigning for
better benefits

34:10.315 --> 34:16.254 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
and pensions for military
veterans. Financial
hardship contributed to his
divorce. Three

34:16.354 --> 34:21.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
of his sons are unemployed. And
he is weary
of politicians manipulating
public opinion.

34:21.593 --> 34:24.763 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
PERO SLAVNIC, Bosnia (through
translator):
I think we are now further away
from being

34:24.863 --> 34:29.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
together without borders than
just after the
war. When foundations are
flawed, you become

34:29.301 --> 34:33.772 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
skeptical about everything,
including the
hand that reaches for you from
the other side.

34:33.872 --> 34:38.076 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We are constantly asking, is
this an honest
hand? We have a lot of problems
in the area

34:38.176 --> 34:39.844 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
of trust.

34:39.945 --> 34:44.783 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: This would have
been the
perfect occasion for the Bosnian
Serb leader,

34:44.883 --> 34:50.088 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Milorad Dodik, to address the
issue of reconciliation.
Of all the dignitaries present,
his words

34:50.188 --> 34:54.859 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
would have carried most
significant, because,
after all, for many Muslims,
Banja Luka represents

34:54.960 --> 34:56.728 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the lion's den.

34:56.828 --> 35:00.532 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He was due to make a keynote
speech, but he
clearly didn't like the tone of
this event

35:00.632 --> 35:06.571 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and elected not to speak. So, to
find out
what he thought, we headed past
the glittering

35:06.671 --> 35:09.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Serb Orthodox church to the
presidential palace
of the Serb Republic.

35:09.975 --> 35:14.179 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILORAD DODIK, President, Serb
Republic (through
translator): I am sorry that
Ferhadija was

35:14.279 --> 35:19.284 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
destroyed. But since then, we
were the ones
to support its reconstruction.
Evil times

35:19.384 --> 35:23.688 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happen. But people can't choose
those times.
We were born in that period.

35:23.788 --> 35:28.626 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But what we can do is to ensure
that we don't
behave in an inhumane way.
Regardless of our

35:28.727 --> 35:32.263 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
religion, nationality and
ideology, we shouldn't
harm each other.

35:32.364 --> 35:37.669 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: But former
Austrian diplomat
Valentin Inzko is skeptical.
He's responsible

35:37.769 --> 35:42.107 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for the civilian implementation
of the Dayton
peace accord and is concerned
that Dodik's

35:42.207 --> 35:48.146 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
threat to secede from Bosnia is
poisoning
the atmosphere.

35:48.246 --> 35:53.651 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
gave some money for this
renovated mosque.
On the other side, the refugee
return is many

35:53.752 --> 35:59.324 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
times not so easy. People have
problems with
papers, et cetera. In schools,
they don't

35:59.424 --> 36:02.494 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
-- they're not allowed them to
speak their
own language.

36:02.594 --> 36:07.032 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He invented a different name for
the Bosnian
language and so on. So we have
to measure

36:07.132 --> 36:09.934 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
him on the ground, in the field.

36:10.035 --> 36:14.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: This student
dormitory in
the wartime Bosnian Serb capital
Pale, a short

36:15.073 --> 36:20.178 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
distance from Sarajevo, is the
most current
source of Inzko's concerns. It
was named in

36:20.278 --> 36:25.583 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
honor of the wartime leader
Radovan Karadzic,
just as he was being sentenced
in late March

36:25.683 --> 36:29.921 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
to 40 years imprisonment for
crimes against
humanity and genocide.

36:30.021 --> 36:36.061 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
VALENTIN INZKO: Imagine in our
country, we
would have such dormitories
glorifying Nazi

36:36.161 --> 36:42.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people, et cetera. It's totally
unacceptable
and this is really something
where Mr. Dodik

36:42.167 --> 36:43.968 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has crossed a red line.

36:44.069 --> 36:48.139 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: In Sarajevo,
besieged for
three years during the war,
Professor Muhamed

36:48.239 --> 36:54.179 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Hamidovic is a symbol of
reconciliation. His
wife was killed by a Serb mortar
fired from

36:54.279 --> 36:59.684 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the surrounding hills. He led
the reconstruction
of the Banja Luka mosque, but he
too is disillusioned.

36:59.784 --> 37:04.489 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MUHAMED HAMIDOVIC, Bosnia
(through translator):
We are still living in the past.
We need a

37:04.589 --> 37:09.794 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
new global system. We need a new
approach
for young people. The current
situation is

37:09.894 --> 37:16.768 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
horrible. I have a son who
doesn't know where
to go or what to do. For five
years, he's

37:16.868 --> 37:22.173 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
unemployed. That's a tragedy.
We're talking
about reconciliation, and that's
so abstract

37:22.273 --> 37:24.042 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to me.

37:24.142 --> 37:28.113 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: Back in Pale,
Radovan Karadzic's
old stomping ground, three young
students

37:28.213 --> 37:33.384 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
are weary of the lack of hope,
and of being
tainted by the Serb wartime
legacy that has

37:33.485 --> 37:35.286 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
nothing to do them.

37:35.386 --> 37:38.523 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANOJELA BOROVCANIN, Bosnian Serb
Law Student:
It is really pointless to make
some differences

37:38.623 --> 37:45.997 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
because people, because we are
all made of
bones and blood. And we are all
here for some

37:46.097 --> 37:51.436 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
reason. We are here to live, and
we are here
to love, and we are here to
improve this world.

37:51.536 --> 37:58.643 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
NENAD SAVIC, Bosnian Serb Law
Student: Bosnia-Herzegovina
is a place with too many fights
between people.

37:58.743 --> 38:02.547 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: They were affected by
everything that
happened here a long time ago
and people think

38:02.647 --> 38:08.453 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
-- still cannot let it go. And
that kind of
depressing. And there is like no
opportunity.

38:08.553 --> 38:14.125 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you go somewhere else, you
see all those
opportunities, and what can you
actually do

38:14.225 --> 38:16.794 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and what you cannot do here in
my country.

38:16.895 --> 38:22.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MALCOLM BRABANT: If the
Ferhadija Mosque is
to be a component in breaking
down the barriers,

38:22.367 --> 38:26.538 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Western officials believe more
Muslims need
to pluck up the courage to
return to their

38:26.638 --> 38:29.541 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
former homes in what is still
the Serb heartland.

38:29.641 --> 38:38.449 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the Serbs also need to offer
genuine guarantees.
Ordinary people on either side
are forging

38:38.550 --> 38:42.921 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
bonds. But it's widely accepted
that politicians
are getting in the way.

38:43.021 --> 38:49.761 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm
Malcolm Brabant
in Banja Luka.

38:49.861 --> 39:01.005 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The past
couple of years
have brought new revelations
about sexual

39:01.105 --> 39:05.944 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
abuse at private schools. At
least eight private
schools in New England have
launched or disclosed

39:06.044 --> 39:08.079 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
investigations this year.

39:08.179 --> 39:13.184 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Now a Boston Globe investigation
has opened
a wider window on the scope of
the problem.

39:13.284 --> 39:18.056 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The report done by the Spotlight
unit that
exposed the sexual abuse scandal
in the church

39:18.156 --> 39:24.562 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
found at least 67 New England
schools have
faced accusations since 1991.
The Globe also

39:24.662 --> 39:31.035 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
found more than 200 former
students say they
have been assaulted or harassed,
and years

39:31.135 --> 39:33.238 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
of alleged cover-ups in some
cases.

39:33.338 --> 39:36.874 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
St. George's School in Rhode
Island is one
school under investigation.

39:36.975 --> 39:43.681 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Anne Scott is a survivor who was
allegedly
raped in 1977 at the school by a
former athletic

39:43.781 --> 39:48.953 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
trainer when she was 15. Her
family later
brought a lawsuit, but the Globe
said the

39:49.053 --> 39:54.158 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
school fought back with its own
suit and pressured
her to sign a gag order.

39:54.259 --> 39:56.094 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Here's part of what she told The
Globe.

39:56.194 --> 40:02.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ANNE SCOTT, Abuse Survivor: They
really turned
hostile and were trying to come
after that,

40:02.800 --> 40:09.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
deposing all our neighbors,
deposing all my
roommates, all community
members.

40:09.540 --> 40:16.481 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, I got shocked. I wasn't as
strong then,
I think, to put it in context,
as I am now.

40:16.581 --> 40:22.553 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And it became a lot of pressure.
I just said,
no amount of money is worth
tearing my family

40:22.654 --> 40:28.126 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
apart.

40:28.226 --> 40:35.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When you are assaulted as a
child and a victim
of rape, you lose your voice.
You lose your

40:35.500 --> 40:44.876 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
soul. You are sort of destroyed
as a person,
your confidence, your
self-image. And the

40:44.976 --> 40:50.114 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
gag order just seals all that
in.

40:50.214 --> 40:54.719 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The trainer
died in 1996.

40:54.819 --> 40:59.991 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Lawyers for victims now say as
many as 50
alumni from the school were
abused, mostly

41:00.091 --> 41:01.392 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
by staff.

41:01.492 --> 41:03.728 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Todd Wallack is a member of the
Spotlight
team, joins me now.

41:03.828 --> 41:07.899 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, give us an idea of how
widespread this
is. This isn't just a couple of
private schools

41:07.999 --> 41:09.734 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in New England.

41:09.834 --> 41:16.040 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TODD WALLACK, The Boston Globe:
No, it's much
wider than a lot of us ever
imagined.

41:16.140 --> 41:23.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We originally started reporting
on this after
Anne Scott, the survivor you
featured, broke

41:23.214 --> 41:28.319 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
her silence, broke the gag order
and spoke
out about the abuse that she
suffered at St.

41:28.419 --> 41:34.158 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
George's in December. And that
prompted other
victims to come forward, many
after decades

41:34.258 --> 41:36.728 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and decades where they had kept
this secret.

41:36.828 --> 41:42.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And we started building a list.
And it kept
getting longer and longer. Some
were reported

41:42.934 --> 41:49.707 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
before individually. Others
hadn't. We looked
through lawsuits. We talked to
lawyers. Since

41:49.807 --> 41:54.145 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
our story on Sunday, we have
been getting
flooded with tips about
additional schools,

41:54.245 --> 42:00.585 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
showing that we have not even
captured the
full scope of all the abuse
that's gone on.

42:00.685 --> 42:04.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Given by the
nature of their
name, private schools, they are
private institutions,

42:04.989 --> 42:11.129 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
do they have to report alleged
-- or abuse
by teachers to the state, like
public schools

42:11.229 --> 42:13.030 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
do?

42:13.131 --> 42:16.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TODD WALLACK: Generally, in
public schools,
teachers are required to be
licensed, and

42:16.367 --> 42:21.038 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
they're overseen by licensing
agencies that
can publicly discipline them and
let other

42:21.139 --> 42:24.475 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
people be aware of potential
problems.

42:24.575 --> 42:29.781 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That isn't true with private
schools, which
generally don't have to license
their educators.

42:29.881 --> 42:34.252 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They're also not subject to
public records
law. They're not overseen by
public school

42:34.352 --> 42:36.287 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
boards with open meetings laws.

42:36.387 --> 42:44.395 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So a lot of this information is
kept secret.
They are able to sign
confidentiality agreements.

42:44.495 --> 42:50.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And for that reason, it allows a
lot of the
abuse to remain secret. It
potentially allows

42:50.735 --> 42:52.537 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
abusers to go to other schools.

42:52.637 --> 42:55.973 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: There were
actually abusers
that were moving from school to
school, but

42:56.073 --> 43:00.511 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
the parents in these new
schools, or the faculty,
nobody actually knew that.

43:00.611 --> 43:02.513 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
TODD WALLACK: Yes, exactly.

43:02.613 --> 43:09.420 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was a person that worked
at St. George's,
for instance, George (sic)
Thompson, who had

43:09.520 --> 43:16.427 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
been accused by, I believe, a
dozen students
of inappropriate touching, went
to another

43:16.527 --> 43:23.835 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
school, Taft, a few years ago
with great recommendations.
And Taft had no idea that he had
been previously

43:23.935 --> 43:25.770 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
subject to those allegations.

43:25.870 --> 43:31.275 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
St. George's hadn't told the
state, and said
at the time they didn't realize.
It was -- fell

43:31.375 --> 43:37.682 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
under the definition of sexual
abuse and needed
to be reported. And we found 11
people who

43:37.782 --> 43:41.052 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
had been accused went on to
other schools.

43:41.152 --> 43:44.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: So, what do
the schools
say? What is their rationale or
justification

43:44.989 --> 43:47.959 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
for taking so long to go public
with this
information?

43:48.059 --> 43:53.564 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
TODD WALLACK: Well, in some
cases, schools
will say a lot of these abuses
happened in

43:53.664 --> 43:59.470 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the '60s or '70s or '80s, and
they now know
more about how to handle it than
they once

43:59.570 --> 44:01.372 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
did.

44:01.472 --> 44:05.276 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some will say that sexual abuse
allegations
are very tricky. They want to
respect the

44:05.376 --> 44:12.149 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
privacy of the victims. They
want to also
be cognizant that they can't
always prove

44:12.250 --> 44:20.024 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
allegations. In a lot of cases,
you have an
alumnus who makes some
accusation, and the

44:20.124 --> 44:23.895 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
staffer is the only other person
who was in
the room, and the staffer denies
it.

44:23.995 --> 44:30.368 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So they say they're trying to be
