can be a neurotoxin.

49:35.973 --> 49:40.911 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JIM PUCKETT: Day in and day out,
these workers
are completely oblivious to this
hazard, are

49:41.011 --> 49:47.151 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
smashing these. The tubes are
breaking right
in front of their faces, and
mercury is very

49:47.251 --> 49:48.319 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
toxic.

49:48.419 --> 49:49.486 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOMAN (through translator): Do
you wear a
mask?

49:49.587 --> 49:51.355 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
MAN (through translator): No.

49:51.455 --> 49:57.194 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WOMAN: I ask him that if he
knows that the
white tubes are dangerous. He
has no idea.

49:57.294 --> 50:02.766 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KATIE CAMPBELL: The United
States is the only
developed nation that hasn't
ratified an international

50:02.867 --> 50:08.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
treaty to stop First World
countries from
dumping e-waste on developing
nations. Other

50:08.906 --> 50:14.311 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
